author: stefan2
msg: Remove the connection setup and repository opening code from the
serve() function such that we may later exit and re-enter it.
Also, we now open the repository in the memory pool passed to
serve() while all other connection_t info gets allocated in the
user socket's pool - with potentially longer lifetime.
(repository_t): Add all information that is static per repository.
Based on that info, we can close and re-open the
repository at any point in the future.
(find_repos): Update signature and allocate the repository object
in a separate pool of (potentially) shorter lifetime.
